 london pioglitazone an anti diabetic drug which goes by the brand name actos boosts the power of anti depressants in patient whether they are suffering from diabetes not according to  new study shahin akhondzadeh professor at the tehran university of medical science in iran and colleagues treated patient with moderate to severe depression with  common antidepressant citalopram either by itself with pioglitazone those who were also given pioglitazone over weeks of treatment reported lower symptoms of depression researchers say it has implication for how diabetes drugs which act in  similar way  actos pioglitazone could be used to boost the effectiveness of existing anti depressants many patient treated with available anti depressant drugs fail to respond to medication the journal neuropsychopharmacology report akhondzadeh said despite the advent of several antidepressant medications the treatment of major depressive disorder mdd is still far from optimal  large proportion of patient with mdd do not respond to their first medication to achieve favourable response these patient are generally treated by either switching to another treatment or with augmentation therapy according to the daily mail actos was licensed in and helps to control blood sugar levels it belongs to  of drugs called thiazolidinediones which are widely used for the treatment of type diabetes resumer chercheur  tester individu antidepresseur antidiabetique connaitre actos verifier  utilite depression patient  diabete averer  prendre actos citalopram  obtenir bout semaine amelioration symptome depressif etude apporter option therapeutique particulier reaffirmer existence lien physiologique diabete depression  mecanisme inflammation commun effet stress mode vie  expliquer lien etroit depression  recurrent maladie cardio vasculaire diabete type

 nouveau antidepresseur rapide efficace  possible enlever idee suicidaire anxiete soulager trouble cognitif ameliorer pronostiquer diminuer risque resistance apporter nouveau option therapeutique tolerer news new antidepressant acts very rapidly and is long lasting drug fights hard to treat depression by targeting brain receptors in  new way text size  mailto fellman northwestern edu joseph moskal evanston ill  first of its kind antidepressant drug discovered by  northwestern university professor and now tested adults who haver failed other antidepressant therapies has been shown to alleviate symptoms within hours haver good safety and produce positif effects that last for about seven days from  single dose the novel therapeutic targets brain receptors responsible for learning and memory  very different approach from existing antidepressants the new drug and others like it also could be helpful in treating other neurological condition including schizophrenia bipolar disorder anxiety and alzheimer s disease the results of the phase iia clinical trial were presented today dec at the st annual meeting of the american college of neuropsychopharmacology in hollywood fla also this week  paper reporting some of the background scientific research that provided the foundation for the clinical development of glyx  was published by the journal the compound called glyx  is the result of more than two decades of work by research professor of biomedical engineering at northwestern s and director of the university s our study showed that this compound is capable of eliciting  robust and rapid antidepressant effect without the typical side effects seen with other drugs that also modulate the nmda receptor said moskal who is founder and chief scientific officer of the evanston based biotechnology company naurex inc which conducted the clinical study glyx  works by modulating the nmda n methyl d aspartate receptor in the brain  do current nmda receptor antagonists such  ketamine but glyx  does not haver their serious and limiting side effects such  hallucination and schizophrenia like effects an antagonist is  substance that inhibits the physiological action of another moskal and his team haver figured  new way to target the nmda receptors that maintains the positif antidepressant properties while eliminating the negative side effects in clinical trial administered at site across the country  single dose of glyx  resulted in significant reductions in depression symptoms among subjects who had shown little improvement with previous drugs subjects had failed treatment with one or more antidepressant agent the positif effects of glyx  were evident within hours and lasted an average of seven days the effect size  measure of the magnitude of the drug s antidepressant efficacy at both these times after  single doser was nearly double the effect size seen with most other antidepressant drugs after four to weeks of repeated dosing side effects of glyx  were mild to moderate and were consister with those observed in subjects receiving  placebo glyx  is  four amino acid peptide that modulates one of  large family of glutamate receptors the nmda n methyl d aspartate receptor in the brain nmda receptors  key role in regulating synaptic plasticity the quality of the connection between neurons and thus are important in regulating learning and memory functions glyx  is administered intravenously moskal said naurex also is working an oral drug with similar properties and potential moskal hopes that these positif glyx  results and the research effort of his team and colleagues will help shepherd in more research and grant support for studying the role of the glutamate mediated processes in neuropsychiatric disorders while the results we are seeing with glyx  are very encouraging i believe the most important research is yet to come moskal said we haver only scratched the surface of the therapeutic potential of the glutamatergic system glyx  currently is undergoing  phase iib clinical trial at site across the united states this trial is evaluating repeated dose of the drug the neuropsychopharmacology paper is titled the research was supported by grants from the ralph and marian falk medical research trust the hope for depression research foundation and the national institutes of health grants mh ns and da northwestern university has exclusively licensed the intellectual property rights related to the therapeutics developed by joseph moskal while at the university to naurex inc northwestern also has  small equity position in naurex  comprendre rester annee  parcourir mise marche distribution  grand echelle  trouver moyen therapeutique viable d agir effet persistant bon tolerance

 the glutamate system and depression researchers haver looked at the role of the glutamate system in depression glutamate is abundant in the brain and is one of the most common neurotransmitters it s involved in memory learning and cognition systeme glutamate depression chercheur  observer role systeme glutamate depression glutamate  abondant cerveau neurotransmetteur frequent  impliquer memoire apprentissage cognition some research has implicated the dysfunction of the glutamate system in medical condition such  huntington s chorea and epilepsy and psychological disorders such  schizophrenia and anxiety disorders recherche  impliquer dysfonction systeme glutamate maladie hutington s chorea epilepsie and desordre psychologique skizophrenie trouble anxieux recent research suggests that drugs targeting  specific type of glutamate receptor in the brain called the nmda receptor may haver antidepressant effects studies haver explored ketamine an nmda antagonist in treating treatment resistant depression and acute suicidal ideation ketamine has  long history in analgesia and anesthesiology currently when  person is at imminent risk for attempting suicider or has attempted suicide they re admitted to  psychiatric hospital and closely monitored but  murrough explained medically there s nothing doctors can do to help with suicidal ideation intense depressed mood antidepressants typically four to weeks to work recherche recent supposer medicament cibler recepteur specifique glutamate cerveau appeler nmda recepteur   effet antidepresseur etude  explorer ketamine nmda antagoniste traitement depression resistant idee suicidaire fort ketamine longue utilisation anasthesie douleur presenter fort idee suicidaire  admettre hopital  docteur   aider cas antidepresseur mettre  semaine  agir ketamine appears to haver fast antidepressant effects within hours  day thus it may help protect patient from suicidal thinking acute dysphoria when they re in the hospital unfortunately its effects only last seven to days this research is highly experimental and probably less than patient in the country haver participated in controlled depression studies of ketamine murrough said the patient in these studies typically haver treatment resistant depression they haven t responded to several antidepressants and haver moderate to severe symptoms of depression they re admitted to the hospital and receive ketamine intravenously from an anesthesiologist while their vital signs are closely monitored ketamine is  drug of abuser known by such street names  special k  it induces trance like hallucination states it also produces mild to moderate cognitif side effects like other anesthetics people report feeling out of it intoxicated and disconnected in general these side effects actually introduce  potential bias to the study design participant know they re getting the treatment when salin is given in the placebo condition murrough said to eliminate this bias murrough and his team are conducting the first ever study to comparer ketamine to  different anesthetic the benzodiazepine midazolam versed which has similar transient effects  ketamine he said the study is currently recruiting participant murrough cautioned that ketamine isn t meant to be  treatment administrated at your doctor s office in  recent article in the journal nature medicine he said ketamine treatment may be akin to electroconvulsive shock treatment studying ketamine may reveal mechanisms underlying depression and help to find drugs that can be prescribed  antidepressants to  wider patient population pharmaceutical companies haver started exploring other nmda receptor antagonists for treatment resistant depression for instance in july the pharmaceutical company evotec neuroscience began testing  compound in  phase ii study which evaluates the safety and efficacy of  drug

 research produces strong evidence for new of antidepressant drugs mar scientists haver shown for the first time that  chemical in the brain called galanin is involved in the risk of developing depression and the research undertaken by  european research team point to  strong reason to develop drugs that modify galanin functioning   new of antidepressant drug galanin is  neuropeptide  small protein that was discovered and investigated over years ago by various group including the swedish scientist tomer hokfelt he is one of the senior authors of the paper published in the journal pnas professor hokfelt and others made the fundamental discovery that neurone can release peptide alongside their classical transmitters and that galanin and noradrenaline are one such pair both haver long been implicated in pain and stress and therefore depression but in the past it had been difficult to study peptide in humans the new research by scientists from sweden hungary and the uk demonstrates that galanin is an importer stress mechanism in the human brain that influencer how sensitif resilient people are to psychosocial stress lead author gabriella juhasz who is  research fellow at the university of manchester and the semmelweis university in budapest said our research show that some version of the gene coding for galanin protect against the risk of depression and anxiety but only in people who haver experienced early life neglect trauma or recent adverse event furthermore the three genes for the three receptors through which galanin acts also influence the risk of depression in people experiencing early recent life adversity crucially all the galanin related genes are widely separated different chromosome and the odds are stacked against four random genes acting in the same way by chance results from the research indicate that although the results are statistically reliable galanin effects modify the substantial effects of stress by only  few percer indeed the moderate overall genetic influence about depression is likely to be mediated by many small genetic effects interacting with each other and with psychosocial factor converging stress mechanism in brain co author professor bill deakin from the university of manchester said the findings provide  strong reason to develop drugs that modify galanin functioning   new of antidepressant drug and new drugs are badly needed  almost all commonly prescribed antidepressants act serotonin and they are often not very effectif our research confirms what previous report haver shown about the variation in the serotonin transporter gene and how it influence the risk of depression we found that the galanin effects are substantially greater than the effects of serotonin the research team also say there is increasing evidence suggesting that depression obesity diabetes and alzheimer s disease may be varying manifestation of shared underlying abnormalities of body metabolism galanin may be part of this general vulnerability since it has  significant role in appetite and obesity added professor deakin

 penser esperance vie patient psychiatre i  e  gens prendre medicament  diminuer moyenner an averer  moyenner an raison probleme cardio vasculaire etats unir esperance vie bipolaire schizophrene traiter  an an population general source volume no january dying too young cardiovascular neglect of the mentally ill henry a  nasrallah md editor in chief current psychiatry henry nasrallah currentpsychiatry com the life span of the seriously mentally ill is even shorter than we had thought earlier studies showed  loss of of the average life span  or to years  recent figure are alarmingly higher however and vary from state to state virginia has the best mortality rate among the seriously mentally ill with  loss of only years of potential life according to the center for mental health service cmhs and the centers for disease control and prevention cdc   perhaps persons who suffer from schizophrenia should move to virginia the loss of potential life years in other states is much worse arizona years texas years missouri years utah years oklahoma years  recent ohio study of mortality and medical illness found an average loss of years of life among persons with schizophrenia  why is the life span of mentally ill persons so short apart from their high rate of death from unnatural cause suicide homicide and accident the most frequent killer is cardiovascular disease high mortality rater are well documented in schizophrenia from various ailments boire especially heart disease  bipolar disorder and major depression are also associated with high death rater from cardiovascular disease  the sad truth is that  dual neglect contributes to premature mortality of the seriously mentally ill the system fails to provide ongoing basic primary healthcare and patient neglect to seek adhere to medical care persons with serious mental illness often haver risk factor associated with preventable cause of heart disease and stroke including smoking obesity sedentary life style and poor nutrition in addition the metabolic syndrome  obesity hypertension hyperglycemia and dyslipidemia  is highly associated with schizophrenia  bipolar disorder  and unipolar depression  cardiovascular risk associated with metabolic syndrome requires ongoing medical follow up which many mentally ill patient do not receive the clinical antipsychotic trial of intervention effectiveness catir found shockingly low treatment rate for diabetes hypertension and hyperglycemia among outpatients with schizophrenia around the country  let us mobilize to correct this shameful health disparity one patient at  time the message to mental health professionals is clear in addition to controlling symptoms of psychosis manier depression or anxiety routinely screen patient for weight gain hypertension high fasting serum glucose and elevated lipid levels refer overweight and obese patient to primary care providers dietitians and exercise counselors to reduce their cardiovascular risks psychiatrists and nurse practitioners must address both mental and medical health needs when formulating assessments treatment plan and patient education for practical recommendations managing medical comorbidities see  point checkup for stable schizophrenia outpatients by britton ashley arey md and stephen r  marder md the public mental health system also could help the seriously mentally ill by integrating primary healthcare with mental healthcare in community settings across the nation there are no excuse to do anything less references newman sc bland rc mortality in  cohort of patient with schizophrenia  record linkage study can j psychiatry    cotton cw manderscheid rw congruencies in increased mortality rater years of potential life lost and cause of death among public mental health client in eight states preventing chronic disease    miller b paschall cb svendsen dp mortality and medical comorbidity among patient with serious mental illness psychiatr serv    meyer jm nasrallah ha eds medical illness and schizophrenia american psychiatric publishing inc washington dc angst f stassen ff clayton pj angst j  mortality of patient with mood disorders follow up over years j affect disord    mcevoy jp meyer jm goff dc al prevalence of the metabolic syndrome in patient with schizophrenia baseline results from the clinical antipsychotic trial of intervention effectiveness catir schizophrenia trial and comparison with national estimates from nhanes iii schizophr res    taylor v macqueen g  association between bipolar disorder and the metabolic syndrome  review j clin psychiatry    heiskamn th niskanen lk hintikka jj al metabolic syndrome and depression  cross sectional analysis j clin psychiatry    nasrallah ha meyer jm goff dc al low rate of treatment for hypertension dyslipidemia and diabetes in schizophrenia dater from the catir schizophrenia trial sample at baseline schizophr res

 articler anglais mettre evidence fait antidepresseur  prendre longue duree soigner depression majeur severe issue tardif  favorable  inverse traitement court suivre recommander inferieur an   prejudiciable bon nombre cas analysis reveals that taking antidepressants for  year or more halves the risk of relaps compared to  shorter course of treatment antidepressant drugs are important in the treatment of depression but how long should people take them for depression is often  chronic problem with relaps being  frequent occurrence researchers in oxford uk haver looked at dater from clinical trial of antidepressants covering around people all had already had treatment with drugs but continued either an antidepressant  placebo the results showed that treating with antidepressants for one two years significantly reduced relaps compared to those placebo the relaps rater actif treatment was per compared with per this is powerful evidence in favor of long term treatment for those suffering from depression indeed there may even be  case for indefinite treatment for those who respond well to antidepressant drugs if their depression is very severe
